<TITLE> Record gold haul for Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb o9 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh's gold haul swelled to 18 in 11th South Asian Games, its highest tally ever in the regional sports extravaganza. The hosts ran away with four gold medals in the penultimate day including football, boxing and wushu to take the third position in medals tally. The Bangladesh Olympic Association had expected to win maximum 17 gold medals, but the athletes proved them wrong. Bangladesh would have much more to show more if they could do better in two key disciplines, athletics and swimming. The football team failed to reach the semifinal in the last two editions but this time they fetched the gold beating Afghanistan 4-o, winning all matches. The cricketers also bagged gold beat Sri Lanka by six runs. The female athletes won eight gold medals while their male teammates secured 10. bdn
